      <prop type="x-source-segment-count">1</prop>
      <prop type="x-target-segment-count">1</prop>
      <prop type="x-chinese-ref">易經 6 judgment</prop>
      <prop type="x-translation-ref">易經 6 judgment</prop>
      <tuv xml:lang="zh-Hant">
        <seg>訟，有孚，窒，惕，中吉，終凶。利見大人，不利涉大川。</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv xml:lang="en">
        <seg>Song intimates how, though there is sincerity in one's contention, he will yet meet with opposition and obstruction; but if he cherish an apprehensive caution, there will be good fortune, while, if he must prosecute the contention to the (bitter) end, there will be evil. It will be advantageous to see the great man; it will not be advantageous to cross the great stream.</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu tuid="yijing-006-song__alignment-002">
      <prop type="x-work-id">yijing</prop>
      <prop type="x-section-id">yijing-006-song</prop>
      <prop type="x-section-unit">section</prop>
      <prop type="x-segment-type">block</prop>
      <prop type="x-alignment-granularity">block</prop>
      <prop type="x-is-coarse-alignment">false</prop>
      <prop type="x-alignment-type">exact_or_near_exact</prop>
      <prop type="x-confidence">1.00</prop>
      <prop type="x-source-segment-count">1</prop>
      <prop type="x-target-segment-count">1</prop>
      <prop type="x-chinese-ref">易經 6 初六</prop>
      <prop type="x-translation-ref">易經 6 初六</prop>
      <tuv xml:lang="zh-Hant">
        <seg>初六，不永所事，小有言，終吉。</seg>
      </tuv>
      <tuv xml:lang="en">
        <seg>The first SIX, divided, shows its subject not perpetuating the matter about which (the contention is). He will suffer the small (injury) of being spoken against, but the end will be fortunate.</seg>
      </tuv>
    </tu>
    <tu tuid="yijing-006-song__alignment-003">
      <prop type="x-work-id">yijing</prop>
